<h2 id="_give_aways_free_gifts">1. Give-aways / free gifts</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Offering <strong>give-aways</strong> or <strong>free gifts</strong> to your customers can help to increase your sales as it encourages your customers to buy more and more frequently. The basic idea is: You promise your customers that you will add a certain item from your portfolio free of charge if their purchase reaches a certain value. Instead of adding these give-aways manually to each order, you can use an <strong><a href="/en/basics/automation/event-procedures">event procedure</a></strong> to automatize this process.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_creating_an_event_procedure">2. Creating an event procedure</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following section explains how you can automatically add certain items to your orders with the help of an event procedure.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating an event procedure for give-aways:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Orders » Event procedures</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>green plus icon</strong> to create a <strong>new event procedure</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a <strong>name</strong> into the editing window, e.g. <strong>Add free item</strong>, and then select <strong>Order generation » New order</strong> as the <strong>event</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>green plus icon</strong> to create a <strong>filter</strong> of the filter type <strong>Order » Order type</strong>. Within this filter, place a check mark for <strong>Order</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>green plus icon</strong> to create a <strong>filter</strong> of the filter type <strong>Order » Value of items (gross)</strong>. Within this filter, enter the desired <strong>value of items</strong> above which you want the customer to receive the free item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>green plus icon</strong> to add a <strong>procedure</strong> of the procedure type <strong>Item » Add item(s)</strong>. Within the procedure, enter the <strong>item ID</strong> of the desired item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>green plus icon</strong> to add a <strong>procedure</strong> of the procedure type <strong>Customer » Send Email</strong>. Within the procedure select your <strong>desired template</strong> and select <strong>Customer</strong> as the recipient. If you have not set up the necessary <strong>E-mail template</strong> yet, go to <strong>Settings » Client (store) » Standard » E-mail » Templates</strong> to do so.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the option <strong>Active</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>save icon</strong> to save the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
